<table border="2" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="6" rules="groups" frame="hsides">


<colgroup>
<col  class="right" />

<col  class="left" />

<col  class="left" />
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="right">predicted \ actual</td>
<td class="left">1</td>
<td class="left">0</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="right">1</td>
<td class="left">true positive</td>
<td class="left">false positive</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="right">0</td>
<td class="left">false negative</td>
<td class="left">true negative</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Definition
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Precision = true positives / no. of PREDICTED positives
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Predicted accuracy
</li>
<li>no. of PREDICTED positives = true positive + false positive
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Recall = true positives / no. of ACTUAL positives
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Actual accuracy
</li>
<li>no. of ACTUAL positives = true positive + false negative
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Examples
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>If we avoid misclassification
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>-&gt; Higher precision, lower recall
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>If we avoid misdiagnosis
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>-&gt; Lower precision, higher recall
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
